{% comment %}
  Local override of al_folio_core's plugins/al_img_tools_scripts.liquid.

  The al_img_tools gem emits `assets/al_img_tools/js/zoom.js` to initialize
  medium-zoom, but that gem asset is regenerated on every build (so a same-path
  local override is overwritten). Instead we capture the gem tag's output and
  point the zoom initializer at a local copy that adds a `margin` option, so
  tall zoomed figures are not clipped at the viewport edges. All other image
  tools emitted by the tag are passed through unchanged, and only a single
  zoom initializer is loaded (no double-binding).
{% endcomment %}
{% capture al_img_tools_scripts_output %}{% al_img_tools_scripts %}{% endcapture %}
{{ al_img_tools_scripts_output | replace: "assets/al_img_tools/js/zoom.js", "assets/js/zoom-margin.js" }}
